SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this Agreement) is made as of December 20, 2019 (the Agreement Date) by and among BITTER RIDGE WIND FARM, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Bitter Ridge and SUN CHIEF SOLAR FARM, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Sun Chief, and SCOUT CLEAN ENERGY LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Manager. Bitter Ridge, Sun Chief and Manager are collectively referred to herein as the Parties and individually as a Party.
RECITALS
A. Bitter Ridge is constructing and will operate an approximately 146.6 MW rated capacity wind generation facility located in Jay County, Indiana, that consists of wind turbine generators, foundations, and towers and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the Bitter Ridge Project.
B. Sun Chief intends to construct and operate an approximately 100 MWac rated capacity solar energy generation facilitye to b located in Jay County, Indiana (the Sun Chief Project.
C. The Parties anticipate that part of the Sun Chief Project will be located on land (such land, the Premises that is subject to existing Bitter Ridge real property interests; the Premises includes the real property described or depicted in Exhibit A-3.
D. Bitter Ridge is designing and constructing, and will own, operate, and maintain, the transmission line and other associated facilities connecting the Bitter Ridge Project to the transmission system owned by AEP Indiana Michigan Transmission Company, Inc. (AEP and controlled by PJM (as defined in Appendix A, all as more particularly described in Exhibit B (the Shared Facilities.
E. Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief desire to share the use and cost of the Shared Facilities, and to engage Manager to operate, maintain, repair and manage the foregoing, all in accordance with and subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement.
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged by the Parties, the Parties agree as follows:
ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATIONS
1.1 Definitions. As used in this Agreement, including the Recitals, and except as required by grammatical usage and apart from proper nouns, each capitalized term has the meaning given to it in this Agreement or in the schedule of Definitions attached as Appendix A.
1.2 Interpretation. In this Agreement, unless a clear, contrary intention appears: (a the singular includes the plural and vice versa; (b reference to any Person includes such

Persons successors and assigns but, in the case of a Co-Tenant, only if such assigns are permitted by this Agreement, and reference to a Person in a particular capacity excludes such Person in any other capacity; (c) reference to any gender includes each other gender; (d) reference to any agreement (including this Agreement), document or instrument means such agreement, document or instrument as amended or modified and in effect from time to time in accordance with the terms thereof and, if applicable, the terms of this Agreement; (e) reference to any Governmental Requirement means such Governmental Requirement as amended, modified, codified, or reenacted, in whole or in part, and in effect from time to time, including, if applicable, rules and regulations promulgated thereunder; (f) reference to any Section means such Section of this Agreement, and references in any Section or definition to any clause means such clause of such Section or definition; (g) hereunder, hereof, hereto and words of similar import shall be deemed references to this Agreement as a whole and not to any particular Section or other provision of this Agreement; (h) including means including without limiting the generality of any description such term; and (i) relative to the determination of any period of time, from means from and including, to means to but excluding and through means through and including.
ARTICLE 2 SHARED FACILITIES
2.1 Conveyance of Proportionate Share. Subject to, and effective upon the (a) delivery by Sun Chief to Bitter Ridge of a written notice confirming that all consents, approvals and actions of, filings with and notices to any Governmental Authority (including the authorizations set forth in Exhibit D) have been obtained or made (as applicable) in connection with the grant, sale, transfer, assignment and conveyance to it of its Proportionate Share; (b) payment by Sun Chief to Bitter Ridge of (i) the Transfer Fee, (ii) the Connection Downtime Net Revenue Loss Payment, and (iii) the Net Revenue Loss Payment; (c) execution of the Shared Metering Agreement, (d) confirmation by the Independent Engineer that the connection of the Sun Chief Project will not cause the Shared Facilities to exceed the Maximum Line Capacity, and (e) satisfaction of the requirements set forth in Section 4.10, Section 4.13(a)(i) and Section 4.13(a)(ii), Bitter Ridge hereby grants, assigns and conveys to Sun Chief an undivided non-exclusive ownership interest in and to the Shared Facilities AS IS, WITH ALL FAULTS AND WITHOUT ANY REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES WHATSOEVER, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, AND SPECIFICALLY EXCLUDING ANY WARRANTY OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR ANY OTHER WARRANTY ARISING UNDER STATUTORY OR COMMON LAW, while at the same time reserving to itself an undivided non-exclusive ownership interest in and to such Shared Facilities, such that each of Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief shall hold an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities, as tenants-in-common, in proportion to its respective Proportionate Share as set forth in Part II of Exhibit C, and in accordance with this Agreement. Prior to the satisfaction of the conditions set forth in this Section 2.1, Bitter Ridge shall hold the Proportionate Share in the Shared Facilities set forth in Part I of Exhibit C. On the Sharing Effective Date, subject to and in accordance with the applicable terms and conditions of this Agreement, Sun Chief shall assume and agree to pay, perform and discharge when due, all Damages and obligations relating to the ownership, possession and use of Sun Chiefs Proportionate Share in the Shared Facilities, arising or to be performed after the Sharing Effective Date.
2 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
2.2 Declaration of Intention. Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief (each, a Co-Tenant and together, the Co-Tenants) hereby declare that beginning on the effective date of the assignment contemplated in Section 2.1 above and the connection of the Sun Chief Project to the Shared Facilities (the Sharing Effective Date), their relationship in and to the Shared Facilities will be as tenants in common, and that each Co-Tenant will have an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities on and subject to the terms, conditions, limitations and requirements set forth in this Agreement in proportion to its Proportionate Share set forth on Part II of Exhibit C. The arrangements and ownership structure contemplated by this Agreement are not being made with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making or sharing in any profits from the ownership or operation of the Shared Facilities, but are instead intended as a form of legal ownership whereby the Co-Tenants can accomplish their respective objectives of independently owning and operating their respective undivided interests in, and sharing the use of, the Shared Facilities in connection with their respective Projects and businesses and to enable the Co-Tenants to perform and discharge certain of their obligations under their respective Interconnection Agreements and their respective Power Purchase Agreements.
2.3 Shared Facilities.
(a) Bitter Ridge plans to procure, install and construct, or has procured, installed and/or constructed, the Shared Facilities. The Shared Facilities are described in Exhibit B. For the avoidance of doubt, unless mutually agreed by the Co-Tenants in writing, the Shared Facilities shall not include any facilities or equipment not described on Exhibit B.
(b) Each Co-Tenant shall own and hold an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities jointly with the other Co-Tenant, as a tenant in common in proportion to its Proportionate Share set forth on Part II of Exhibit C for the benefit, operation and use of its respective Project as provided herein; provided that Sun Chief shall not own or hold an interest in the Shared Facilities prior to the Sharing Effective Date.
(c) Subject to the other rights, obligations and limitations set forth in this Agreement, each Co-Tenant may use the Shared Facilities (i) to connect its Project to the Shared Facilities and (ii) only to transmit electrical energy bi-directionally to and from its Project to the point of interconnection with the Transmission Owner. Any Damages incurred by Bitter Ridge arising from Sun Chiefs use of Backfeed Power from the Shared Facilities shall be addressed in the Shared Metering Agreement. Neither Co-Tenant will provide any interconnection or transmission services or rights to the other Co-Tenant.
2.4 Real Property Rights.
(a) Consent. Subject to subsection (b) below, Bitter Ridge hereby consents and agrees to the acquisition by Sun Chief of separate real property interests in the Premises for the purposes of locating and/or operating the Sun Chief Project, regardless of whether such interests overlap with Bitter Ridges property rights and any interests in and to the Bitter Ridge Property. Such consent shall not be considered or construed as a subordination of Bitter Ridges real property rights and interests to any separate real property rights and interests obtained by Sun Chief.
3 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
(b) Separate Interests in the Premises. Other than as set forth under this Agreement with respect to the Shared Facilities, each Co-Tenant shall take steps to acquire and perfect separate real property interests to the extent required for the location and/or operation of its Project and shall bear all costs and expenses and comply with all Governmental Requirements pertaining thereto. To the extent that either Co-Tenants separate property interest overlaps with the other Co-Tenants interests, the Co-Tenants shall work together in good faith to ensure that the operation of each Co-Tenants Project does not unreasonably interfere with the property rights of the other Co-Tenant in and to such lands. Neither Co-Tenant shall have the right to: (i) interfere with the other Co-Tenants Project or property rights, except as specifically provided in this Agreement, (ii) cause the termination of the other Co-Tenants property rights, (iii) relocate or cause the unapproved relocation of any of the other Co-Tenants Project facilities, or (iv) purport to act as the agent of the other Co-Tenant in discussions or negotiations with the fee simple owners of the real property included in the Co-Tenants Projects.
(c) Access to Real Property; Crossing Agreements. Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief each grants to the other Co-Tenant, the right to cross over, under and onto the other Co-Tenants Property, as applicable, for the purpose of locating each Co-Tenants transmission line and connecting such line to the Shared Facilities. The locations of all crossings by one Co-Tenant of the other Co-Tenants pre-existing Project facilities shall be at locations approved by the Co- Tenant owning the pre-existing facilities in its commercially reasonable discretion. Each Co- Tenant further grants to the other Co-Tenant, the right of ingress and egress to and from its Property, solely to the extent required to exercise such other Co-Tenants rights and perform its obligations hereunder with respect to the Shared Facilities. No separate crossing agreement or consent or approval shall be required for the exercise of the real property rights granted hereunder.
2.5 Access to the Shared Facilities.
(a) By Co-Tenants. Subject to the conditions and additional rights described below, each Co-Tenant shall have access to and the right to enter onto the Shared Facilities to the extent reasonably necessary for (i) inspection of such Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the other Co-Tenant or the Manager and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities in the event the Manager fails to do so, in accordance with the terms hereof, or (iii) ingress and egress to and from, and for maintenance or repair of, the Shared Facilities in the event of an Emergency and the failure or unavailability of the Manager or its representatives to respond to such Emergency in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. Except in the event of an Emergency, the accessing Co-Tenant shall give the other Co-Tenant and the Manager at least forty-eight (48) hours prior notice of its intent to access the Shared Facilities (said notice may be by telephone, e-mail, or any other recognized electronic means in addition to any other methods of notice authorized herein). In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required, but the Co-Tenant shall give notice of its intent to access the Shared Facilities as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter. Any Co-Tenant accessing the Shared Facilities shall follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Co-Tenants and/or the Manager with respect to the Shared Facilities or otherwise applicable to the Shared Facilities. Notwithstanding the above, each Co-Tenant may enter upon any real property separately held by it pursuant to a lease, easement or other individual real property interest without the need to give prior notice or obtain consent as
4 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
provided in this Section 2.5(a) unless such entry is with respect to the Shared Facilities located thereon and then only to the extent set forth above.
(b) By Manager. The Manager shall have access to the Shared Facilities at any time for purposes of complying with its obligations set forth in this Agreement, including (i) inspection of such Shared Facilities located thereon, without unduly interfering with the normal operations of the Co-Tenants and otherwise subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, (ii) Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms hereof, or (iii) ingress and egress to and from the Shared Facilities. The Manager shall follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by each Co-Tenant with respect to its real property interests in the Projects or otherwise applicable to the Shared Facilities, where the terms thereof have been made available to the Manager.
(c) By Financing Parties. A Financing Party of a Co-Tenant shall have the right to access the Shared Facilities for the purposes described in Section 2.5(a)(i) and, in connection with or following the exercise of remedies by a Financing Party under its respective Financing Documents, for the other purposes described in Section 2.5(a), in each case upon five (5) Business Days advance written notice of its entry delivered to the Manager and the other Co-Tenant; provided that such right of entry shall be limited to normal business hours except in the case of an Emergency. Any Financing Party so accessing the Shared Facilities shall follow all written safety and security procedures and other site regulations of the Co-Tenants and/or the Manager with respect to the Shared Facilities or otherwise applicable to the Shared Facilities that do not unduly interfere with the normal operations of the Co-Tenants and the Manager thereon, where the terms thereof have been made available to such Financing Party.
2.6 No Interference.
(a) Each Co-Tenants use of the Shared Facilities shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by any other Co-Tenant of its respective rights in such Shared Facilities, subject to all the terms and provisions of this Agreement. The Co-Tenants shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate each Co-Tenants use of the Shared Facilities for the benefit of such Co-Tenants Project. Subject to the first sentence of this Section 2.6, the use of the Shared Facilities by the Co- Tenants pursuant to and in accordance with the terms of this Agreement will not, separately or in the aggregate, be deemed to constitute an overburdening of the Shared Facilities or any portion of it.
(b) Sun Chief shall, at all times, maintain a minimum set back distance of 600ft between the facilities comprising the Sun Chief Project and each wind turbine that is part of the Bitter Ridge Project.
2.7 Construction of Shared Facilities; Connection.
(a) Construction of Shared Facilities. Bitter Ridge, or its designee, shall procure, install and construct the Shared Facilities in a good and workmanlike manner and in accordance with applicable Governmental Requirements.

(b) Connection of Sun Chief Project. When connecting its Project to the Shared Facilities, Sun Chief shall, to the fullest extent commercially reasonable and subject to Good Utility Practice, (i) limit any interference with the use by Bitter Ridge of the Shared Facilities during such installation and connection activities, and (ii) (A) schedule during an off-peak and/or low wind down-time period any required disconnection of the Bitter Ridge Project to conduct construction activities in order to minimize the impact on the Bitter Ridge Project, and (B) provide at least thirty (30) days prior written notice to Bitter Ridge and Manager of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, including dates and times of construction activities and disconnection.
(c) Connection Costs.
(i) No less than 60 days prior to Substantial Completion of the Sun Chief Project, Sun Chief shall provide to Bitter Ridge notice detailing the anticipated nameplate capacity of the Sun Chief Project and any upgrades or installations required to be made to the Shared Facilities to facilitate the connection of the Sun Chief Project to the Shared Facilities.
(ii) All costs and expenses associated with interconnecting the Sun Chief Project into the Shared Facilities (including the procurement and installation of any facilities, improvements, modifications or upgrades of facilities to permit Sun Chief to utilize the Shared Facilities) shall be for the account of, and paid for, by Sun Chief, regardless of whether or not such facilities benefit Bitter Ridge.
(iii) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, each Co- Tenant shall be solely responsible for the payment of any and all grid interconnection or other charges, registration costs, or other fees or costs related to the delivery of electrical energy generated by its Project to the Shared Facilities, including any charges, fees or costs for scheduling, imbalance, or ancillary services.
2.8 Additional Premises Rights or Facilities.
(a) Approval of Additional Premises Rights or Facilities. To the extent that any additional premises or rights in premises that relate to the Shared Facilities or operation thereof (the Additional Premises Rights) or any additional facilities, improvements, modifications, or upgrades of facilities that relate to the Shared Facilities or operation thereof (Additional Facilities) (i) are required in order to construct, use, operate, maintain or repair the Shared Facilities, (ii) are required by either Co-Tenant for the construction, use, operation, maintenance or repair of its Project, or (iii) are needed or would materially benefit, in the reasonable belief of the Manager, the interconnection or operation of the Projects collectively, a Co-Tenant or the Manager, as applicable, may give written notice to the other Parties requesting the other Co-Tenant or both Co-Tenants, as applicable, to approve such Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities, with a reasonable explanation why such Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities are needed and demonstrating that such Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities will not, taken as a whole, have an adverse effect on the Shared Facilities or any Project.
(i) Each Co-Tenant shall, within thirty (30) days after receiving such notice, notify the Manager and the other Co-Tenant in writing of its election to participate or not

to participate in such Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities, as applicable. Failure to notify the other Co-Tenant of its election to participate shall be deemed an election not to participate.
(ii) If acquisition of the Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities is approved by each Co-Tenant with a Proportionate Share, they shall be acquired in the name of the Co-Tenants as tenants in common and shall become Shared Facilities, as applicable, hereunder.
(iii) Following acquisition of any Additional Premises Rights and/or Additional Facilities, the Parties will amend Exhibits A-1, A-2 and B as necessary to reflect such new Shared Facilities.
(b) Disapproved Additional Premises Rights or Additional Facilities. If any proposed Additional Premises Rights or Additional Facilities are not approved pursuant to the provisions of Section 2.8(a) above, but the requirements of Section 2.8(c) below are satisfied and any additional facilities, improvements, modifications or upgrades are constructed and installed in accordance with Governmental Requirements and Good Utility Practice, then nothing herein shall prevent a Co-Tenant from acquiring such property rights (Disapproved Additional Premises Rights) or installing such additional facilities, improvements, modifications or upgrades (Disapproved Additional Facilities) in its own name. Any such Disapproved Additional Premises Rights and Disapproved Additional Facilities shall not be deemed Shared Facilities hereunder.
(c) Requirements of All Additional Premises Rights and Additional Facilities.
(i) No Additional Premises Rights (including any Disapproved Additional Premises Rights) shall be acquired by any Co-Tenant, and no Additional Facilities (including any Disapproved Additional Facilities) may be acquired, constructed or installed by any Co-Tenant, if such acquisition, construction or installation could reasonably be expected to (i) result in an Emergency, (ii) violate the terms of this Agreement, any Interconnection Agreement, any Power Purchase Agreement, any Land Matters, any Governmental Requirements or any Security Documents, or (iii) have any more than a de mininis adverse effect on the operation, performance, reliability or maintenance costs of any other Project (except as may be agreed by the Party owning such affected Project in writing in its sole discretion), or the operation, performance, reliability or Operation and Maintenance costs of the Shared Facilities; provided, however, that if requested by the Co-Tenant proposing to acquire, construct or install the Additional Premises Rights or Additional Facilities that comply with the requirements set forth in the immediately preceding sentence, a Co-Tenant will, at the sole cost and expense of the requesting Co-Tenant, use commercially reasonable efforts to obtain any necessary consents under the Security Documents related to its Project to allow the acquisition, construction and/or installation of such Additional Premises Rights or Additional Facilities.
(ii) Any Co-Tenant installing Additional Facilities or Disapproved Additional Facilities, or performing maintenance or other repairs of the Shared Facilities shall to the fullest extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak and/or down-time period any required disconnection or downtime of the Shared Facilities in order to minimize the impact

on the Projects. In addition, any Co-Tenant installing Additional Facilities or Disapproved Additional Facilities shall provide at least thirty (30) days prior written notice to the other Co- Tenant of (i) commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, and take into consideration, to the fullest extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction required by the other Co-Tenant and (ii) any planned outages, and the duration thereof, of the Shared Facilities that would result in a disconnection of the other Co-Tenants Project; provided that the other Co-Tenant shall not attempt to interfere with the installation of the proposed Additional Facilities or Disapproved Additional Facilities, unless such installation can reasonably be expected to result in an Emergency or violate the terms of, this Agreement, an Interconnection Agreement, a Power Purchase Agreement, Land Matters, such other Co-Tenants contracts or agreements to deliver energy into the PJM market, any Governmental Requirements or any Security Document. The Co-Tenant installing the Additional Facilities or Disapproved Additional Facilities, as applicable, will indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Co-Tenant from any and all Damages arising from such construction or installation activities and any resultant disconnection or curtailment of the other Co-Tenants facilities.
2.9 Covenants Running with the Land. The covenants of the Co-Tenants made in this Agreement shall be deemed to be covenants running with and binding upon the land pursuant to Governmental Requirements for the duration of the term of this Agreement and shall bind and benefit all current and future owners of the lands bound and benefited by this Agreement, including the Sun Chief Property, the Bitter Ridge Property and the Premises.
2.10 Liens. No Party shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur or permit or suffer by, through, or under such Party to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities, either as a whole or in a Partys undivided interest therein, except for (a) liens for financing purposes as provided in Section 8.3, and (b) Permitted Encumbrances. If any lien not permitted under the previous sentence attaches to any of the Shared Facilities, or if a Party receives notice of any such lien, the Party whose actual or alleged act or omission resulted in such lien shall cause such lien to be released and removed of record within ninety (90) days of such attachment or notice. Failure of a Party to remove such lien as required under this Section 2.10 shall entitle each other Party to cause such lien to be removed and the costs thereof shall be promptly reimbursed by the Party responsible hereunder for removal of such lien.
ARTICLE 3 PAYMENT OF O&M EXPENSES
3.1 Expenses of Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities. The Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities shall be performed in accordance with the requirements set forth in Article 5 below. From and after the Sharing Effective Date, the expenses of such Operation and Maintenance shall be allocated among the Co-Tenants and paid as provided in this Article 3. Each Co-Tenant shall be responsible for and shall pay its Proportionate Share of the expenses and liabilities relating to the Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities, including all allocable payments under the O&M Agreement, the Management Fee, all FERC compliance costs, NERC compliance costs, costs of compliance with other Governmental
8 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
Requirements, costs of labor and materials and accounting, general and administrative costs (collectively, Shared O&M Expenses).
3.2 Management Fee. From the Sharing Effective Date until completion by the Manager of its services hereunder upon termination of this Agreement, the Co-Tenants shall pay as part of the Shared O&M Expenses and in accordance with their Proportionate Share, a fee of per year (the Management Fee) to the Manager for its services hereunder. The Management Fee shall be pro-rated for any partial year during which the Manager provides services, and payable quarterly in advance. The Management Fee shall escalate each year at the rate of beginning on the first anniversary of the Sharing Effective Date.
3.3 Invoicing, Late Payments.
(a) The Manager shall be responsible for invoicing each Co-Tenant for its applicable Proportionate Share of the Shared O&M Expenses relating to the Shared Facilities. Each such invoice shall be payable by the invoiced Co-Tenant within thirty (30) days after receipt of an invoice, with backup documentation, from the Manager setting forth the amount that is due. If a Co-Tenant disputes the invoiced amount, it shall nonetheless pay the disputed amount, and shall refer the issue for resolution in accordance with provisions of Article 13. Any disputed amount that is finally determined by dispute resolution pursuant to Article 13 or by mutual agreement to have been improperly invoiced shall be promptly refunded to the Co-Tenant. All sums not paid when due shall thereafter bear interest at the Default Interest Rate. Each Co-Tenant shall have the right to audit, and receive supporting documentation for, any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by such Co-Tenant hereunder.

MEMORANDUM OF SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS MEMORANDUM OF SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (Memorandum) is made and entered into as this _____ day of ____________________, 2019, (the Agreement Date) by and between BITTER RIDGE WIND FARM, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Bitter Ridge) and SUN CHIEF SOLAR FARM, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Sun Chief), and SCOUT CLEAN ENERGY LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Manager). Each of Bitter Ridge, Sun Chief and Manager are collectively referred to herein as the as the Parties and individually as a Party. Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief are sometimes each referred to herein as a Co-Tenant and together as the Co- Tenants.
RECITALS
A. Bitter Ridge is constructing and will operate an approximately 146.6 MW rated capacity wind generation facility located in Jay County, Indiana, that consists of wind turbine generators, foundations, and towers and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the Bitter Ridge Project). The Bitter Ridge Project will be located on in the Bitter Ridge Property (so called herein) described on Exhibit A-1 to this Memorandum.
B. Sun Chief intends to construct and operate an approximately 100 MWac rated capacity solar energy generation facility to be located in Jay County, Indiana (the Sun Chief Project). The Sun Chief Project will be located on in the Sun Chief Property (so called herein) described on Exhibit A-2 to this Memorandum. The Bitter Ridge Project and Sun Chief Project are sometimes each referred to herein as a Project and together as the Projects.
C. The Parties anticipate that part of the Sun Chief Project will be located on land (such land, the Premises) that is subject to existing Bitter Ridge real property interests; the Premises includes the real property described or depicted in Exhibit A-3 to this Memorandum. Exhibit E
Page 1 of 9 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
D. Bitter Ridge is designing and constructing, and will own, operate, and maintain certain shared facilities (such facilities, the Shared Facilities), for the exclusive benefit, operation and use of the Projects in accordance with that certain Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of the date hereof by and among the Parties (the Shared Facilities Agreement).
E. Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief desire to share the use and cost of the Shared Facilities, and to engage Manager to operate, maintain, repair and manage the foregoing, all in accordance with and subject to the terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement.
NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, the Parties hereby certify as follows:
1. Declaration of Intention. On and subject to the terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement, the Parties hereby declare that the relationship of Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief in and to the Premises and the Shared Facilities is and shall remain that of tenants in common, that each of Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief has separate real estate interests in the Premises and an undivided interest in the Shared Facilities in proportion to such Project Companys Proportionate Share (as defined in the Shared Facilities Agreement).
2. Properties Benefitted and Bound. The rights and obligations of the Parties under the Shared Facilities Agreement benefit and burden each of the Bitter Ridge Property, the Sun Chief Property, and the Premises, and the covenants and obligations under the Shared Facilities Agreement are and shall be considered covenants running with the land. All sales, conveyances and other transfers of any interests in the Bitter Ridge Property, the Sun Chief Property, and the Premises shall be subject to all of the terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement, whether or not expressly stated in any instrument of sale, conveyance or transfer.
3. Real Property Rights; Consent. Subject to subsection (b) below, in the Shared Facilities Agreement Bitter Ridge consented and agreed to the acquisition by Sun Chief of separate real property interests in the Premises for the purposes of locating and/or operating the Sun Chief Project, regardless of whether such interests overlap with Bitter Ridges property rights and any interests in and to the Bitter Ridge Property. Such consent shall not be considered or construed as a subordination of Bitter Ridges real property rights and interests to any separate real property rights and interests obtained by Sun Chief.
(b) Separate Interests in the Premises. Other than as set forth under the Shared Facilities Agreement with respect to the Shared Facilities, each Co-Tenant agreed to take steps to acquire and perfect separate real property interests to the extent required for the location and/or operation of its Project and shall bear all costs and expenses and comply with all Governmental Requirements (as defined in the Shared Facilities Agreement) pertaining thereto. To the extent that either Co-Tenants separate property interest overlaps with the other Co-Tenants interests, the Co-Tenants shall work together in good faith to ensure that the operation of each Co-Tenants Project does not materially interfere with the property rights of the other Co-Tenant in and to such lands. Neither Co-Tenant shall have the right to: (i) materially interfere with the other Co-Tenants Project or property rights, (ii) cause the termination of the other Co-Tenants property rights, (iii) relocate or cause Exhibit E
Page 2 of 9 PUBLIC VERSION CUI//PRIV Information Has Been Removed
the unapproved relocation of any of the other Co-Tenants Project facilities, or (iv) purport to act as the agent of the other Co-Tenant in discussions or negotiations with the fee simple owners of the real property included in the Co-Tenants Projects.
(c) Access to Real Property; Crossing Agreements. In the Shared Facilities Agreement, Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief each grant to the other Co-Tenant, the right to cross over, under and onto the other Co-Tenants Project, as applicable, for the purpose of locating each Co-Tenants transmission line and connecting such line to the Shared Facilities. The locations of all crossings by one Co-Tenant of the other Co-Tenants pre- existing Project facilities shall be at locations approved by the Co-Tenant owning the pre- existing facilities in its commercially reasonable discretion. Each Co-Tenant further grants to the other Co-Tenant, the right of ingress and egress to and from its Property, solely to the extent required to exercise such other Co-Tenants rights and perform its obligations under the Shared Facilities Agreement with respect to the Shared Facilities. No separate crossing agreement or consent or approval shall be required for the exercise of the real property rights granted in the Shared Facilities Agreement.
4. Waiver of Right to Partition or Distribution. Under the Shared Facilities Agreement, each Party has acknowledged and agreed that it would be prejudicial to the interests of the Parties thereunder if any Party were to seek partition or any other type of division of the Shared Facilities or any other shared rights, assets or properties, or to file an action for such partition or division. Therefore, in consideration of such fact and for other good and valuable consideration, each of the Parties has waived and relinquished any and all rights that it may have to seek a partition or any other type of division of any rights or interests in the Shared Facilities or any other shared rights, assets or properties that are subject to the Shared Facilities Agreement.
5. Incorporation; Conflicts. The terms and conditions of the Shared Facilities Agreement are incorporated herein by reference. In the event of any conflict between the provisions of the Shared Facilities Agreement and the provisions of this Memorandum, the Shared Facilities Agreement shall control. This Memorandum may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an original and all of which, taken together, shall constitute one agreement.

ASSIGNMENT AND ASSUMPTION AGREEMENT (REMOVAL AND REPLACEMENT OF MANAGER OF SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT)
This Assignment and Assumption Agreement (this Agreement), dated as of August 23, 2024 (the Effective Date) is made by and between Scout Clean Energy LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Incumbent Manager), Scout Operating Partners LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (New Manager) and Bitter Ridge Wind Farm, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Bitter Ridge), and Sun Chief Solar Farm, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Sun Chief). Bitter Ridge and Sun Chief are collectively referred to herein as Co- Tenants and individually as an Co-Tenant.
RECITALS
A. Co-Tenants entered into that certain Shared Facilities Agreement, dated as of December 20, 2019, with Incumbent Manager (the SF Agreement) for shared facility and management services with respect to the approximately 146 MW wind-powered operational electrical generation facility known as the Bitter Ridge Project and the approximately 100 MWac rated capacity solar energy generation facility under development known as the Sun Chief Project, both described therein.
B. Co-Tenants have agreed to remove the Incumbent Manager and replace the Incumbent Manager with the New Manager.
C. All other necessary consents have been received in connection with the execution and delivery of this Agreement.
NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the parties hereby agree as follows:
AGREEMENT
1. Capitalized Terms. Capitalized terms used but not defined in this Agreement shall have the meaning given to them in the SF Agreement.
2. Removal of Incumbent Manager. Pursuant to Section 6.5(c) of the SF Agreement, Co-Tenants hereby agree to remove the Incumbent Manager, without cause, from its position as Manager (the Removal).
3. Appointment of New Manager. Pursuant to Section 6.5(d) of the SF Agreement, Co-Tenants hereby agree to appoint the New Manager as Manager under the SF Agreement. Such appointment of the New Manager shall take effect on the Effective Date.
4. Agreement of Incumbent Manager. Incumbent Manager, by its signature hereto, acknowledges it has received this Agreement, and this Agreement satisfies the written notice requirement pursuant to 6.5(c) of the SF Agreement. For the avoidance of doubt, the Incumbent Manager hereby waives any notice requirements pursuant to 6.5(c) of the Agreement. From the date hereof, Incumbent Manager shall be released from, and New Manager shall assume, the
-1- OHSUSA:767908450.1
liabilities, obligations, commitments, and responsibilities of Incumbent Manager with respect to the SF Agreement, solely to the extent arising on or after the Effective Date.
5. Agreement of New Manager. New Manager, by its signature hereto, hereby agrees to assume and accept the position of Manager under the SF Agreement as of the Effective Date. For the avoidance of doubt, the Incumbent Manager hereby waives any notice requirements pursuant to the Agreement. From the Effective Date, Incumber Manager shall be released from, and New Manager shall assume, the liabilities, obligations, commitments, and responsibilities of Incumbent Manager with respect to the SF Agreement, solely to the extent arising on or after the Effective Date.
6. Governing Law. This Agreement, and any instrument or agreement required hereunder (to the extent not otherwise expressly provided for therein), shall be governed by, and construed in accordance with, the laws of the State of Indiana applicable to contracts made and to be performed within the State of Indiana and without reference to the choice of law principles of the State of Indiana or any other state.
7. Further Assurances. Each of the parties hereto covenants and agrees, without further consideration, to execute and deliver such further documents, instruments and notices and to perform such other acts as may be reasonably necessary or proper and usual to effect this Agreement and to more fully assure the assignees, their successors and assigns all of the rights and interests hereby assigned, conveyed and transferred or intended to be so assigned, conveyed and transferred.
8. Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in counterparts, with each counterpart will be deemed to be an original instrument and all counterparts taken together will constitute one agreement. Executed copies of this Agreement may be delivered by facsimile, PDF, or email and shall be deemed originals and binding upon the parties hereto.
9. Amendments. No provision of this Agreement may be amended, modified or waived except by written agreement duly executed by each of the parties.
10. Successors and Assigns. This Agreement shall be binding upon and shall inure to the benefit of the parties and their respective personal representatives, heirs, successors and assigns.
